# CodeAlpha Cyber Security Internship  
## Task 1: Advanced Network Packet Sniffer (Python + Scapy)

This project is developed as part of the **CodeAlpha Cyber Security Internship Program**.  
The task focuses on building an **intermediate-level network packet sniffer** capable of analyzing live network traffic at multiple protocol layers.

This tool provides detailed inspection of Ethernet, IP, TCP, UDP, and ICMP packets using the Scapy library.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Features

### âœ… Layer-Wise Packet Analysis  
- Ethernet Layer  
- IP Layer  
- TCP/UDP Layer  
- ICMP Layer  

### âœ… Displays Critical Information  
- Source & Destination IP  
- Source & Destination MAC Addresses  
- Protocol Information (TCP/UDP/ICMP/Other)  
- TTL (Time to Live)  
- Fragment Offset  
- Flags  
- Packet Length  
- Timestamp  
- Payload Contents  

### âœ… Advanced TCP/UDP/ICMP Insights  
- TCP sequence & acknowledgment numbers  
- TCP flags  
- UDP source/destination ports  
- ICMP type & code  
- Raw payload extraction  

### âœ… Real-Time Sniffing  
Uses Scapy's `sniff()` function to capture packets continuously.

